SELECT MIN(t.title) AS typical_european_movie
 FROM sampled_company_type_1 AS ct,
 sampled_info_type_1 AS it,
 sampled_movie_companies_1 AS mc,
 sampled_movie_info_1 AS mi,
 sampled_title_1 AS t
 WHERE t.id = mi.movie_id
 AND t.id = mc.movie_id
 AND mc.movie_id = mi.movie_id
 AND ct.id = mc.company_type_id
 AND it.id = mi.info_type_id
 AND ct.kind = '@param0'
 AND mc.note LIKE '@param1'
 AND mc.note LIKE '@param2'
 AND mi.info IN ('@param3')
 AND t.production_year > @param4;

He is usually only referenced by his title "CINCPACFLT" - Commander-In-Chief, Pacific Fleet. It is an old Naval tradition that a captain, and by extension any commanding officer, is not just himself, he is his command and, on certain occasions, such as when arriving or departing a naval warship, is always identified as the command, never by name. The main reason the film was not shown inside Germanic Europe is because of the serious historical inaccuracy to both the AnschluÃ of Austria and the Nazi Party being portrayed inaccurately, just in general. Even before it came out, Hedy Lamarr warned the studio not to show it inside Germanic Europe, because she knew how the men, especially, would react, but the studio executives laughed her off. Several other famous Germanic Europeans also did not take kindly to the film, becoming quite vocal, including: Peter Lorre, who had seen the Broadway play, Marlene Dietrich, Eva Gabor, Conrad Veidt, Audrey Hepburn, Werner Klemperer, John Banner, Fritz Lanf, Karl Freud, Robert Clary and Erich Plommer. It is what caused the studio to pull the film from cinemas six months before they intended to, causing them to actually lose money on its first release. It was not until the late 1970s when the film would actually break even.', 'UK:17 November 1961', 'Japan:11 March 1995', 'UK:23 December 1982', 'USA:13 May 1971
